### Secondary Navigation (Breadcrumbs)
Each page includes contextual breadcrumbs for improved SEO and navigation:

```
Home > Migration Guide > Implementation > Configuration
Home > Migration Guide > Troubleshooting > Build Errors
Home > Migration Guide > Best Practices > Performance
```

## Link Building Strategy

### 1. Contextual Internal Linking

#### Within Main Guide (`migration-back-guide.md`)
- **Assessment Section** â†’ Links to implementation checklist
- **Benefits Section** â†’ Links to performance comparison in case studies
- **Implementation Overview** â†’ Deep links to detailed implementation guide
- **Troubleshooting Preview** â†’ Links to specific troubleshooting sections
- **Best Practices Summary** â†’ Links to detailed best practices guide
- **Case Studies Preview** â†’ Links to relevant case studies

#### Cross-Pillar Linking
- **Implementation Guide** â†’ Back to main guide, forward to troubleshooting
- **Troubleshooting Guide** â†’ Links to both implementation and best practices
- **Best Practices Guide** â†’ Links to all other pillars
- **Case Studies** â†’ Links to relevant implementation and best practices sections

### 2. Link Placement Strategy

#### Top-of-Page Links
- Quick navigation to main sections
- "Related Articles" sidebar
- "Next Steps" call-to-action

#### Mid-Content Links
- Contextual links to related sections
- "Learn More" callouts
- Code example references

#### Bottom-of-Page Links
- "Continue Reading" section
- "Related Resources" compilation
- "Get Help" contact information

### 3. Anchor Text Strategy

#### Primary Keywords (Exact Match)
- "vite to nextjs migration"
- "nextjs migration guide"
- "nextjs implementation"
- "troubleshooting nextjs"

#### Long-tail Keywords (Partial Match)
- "how to migrate from vite to nextjs"
- "nextjs migration best practices"
- "common nextjs migration problems"
- "nextjs performance optimization"

#### Branded Keywords
- "migration guide"
- "implementation guide"
- "troubleshooting guide"
- "best practices guide"

